  "prompt": "Why Arnab Goswami resign times now? And start entrepreneurs.?",
  "response": "Arnab Goswami, a prominent Indian journalist and television news anchor, resigned from Times Now in November 2016. His departure from the channel was reportedly due to differences with the management of the Times Group, the parent company of Times Now. There were speculations about editorial disagreements and issues related to his contract.\n\nFollowing his resignation, Arnab Goswami founded his own media venture, ARG Outlier Media, and launched a new television news channel called Republic TV in May 2017. Republic TV quickly gained popularity and became known for its aggressive style of journalism, often focusing on political debates and breaking news.\n\nGoswami's decision to start his own venture was driven by his desire to have more editorial control and to build a media platform aligned with his vision of journalism. His entrepreneurial move allowed him to create a successful media company that has expanded to include multiple channels and digital platforms.\n\nIn summary, Arnab Goswami resigned from Times Now due to differences with the management and started his own entrepreneurial venture to gain more control over his work and to pursue his vision of journalism.",
